<p class="rubric">Saturday — All Saints and the Faithful Departed</p>
<p>
	<span class="rubric">Troparion:</span> O Apostles, martyrs, prophets, hierarchs, righteous and just ones, who have finished the course and kept the faith: Seeing that you have boldness with the Savior, beseech Him for us that our souls may be saved.
</p>
<p>
	Keep Thy servants in remembrance, O Lord, since Thou art good, and do Thou forgive their every sin in this life; for no man is without sin, except for Thee, who art able to grant rest to those who have even departed from this life.
</p>
<p>
	<span class="rubric">Theotokion:</span> O Holy Mother of the Ineffable Light, with reverence we magnify you, honoring you with angelic hymns.
</p>
